            },
            {
                "s2_paper_id": "50d7c94d54b227dc2da8e9ccc87f95c61a9e2c24",
                "title": "Exchange-Correlation Energy from Green's Functions.",
                "year": 2024,
                "venue": "Physical Review Letters",
                "citation_count": 2,
                "reference_count": 56,
                "abstract": "Density-functional theory (DFT) calculations yield useful ground-state energies and densities, while Green's function techniques (such as GW) are mostly used to produce spectral functions. From the Galitskii-Migdal formula, we extract the exchange correlation of DFT directly from a Green's function. This spectral representation provides an alternative to the fluctuation-dissipation theorem of DFT, identifying distinct single-particle and many-particle contributions. Results are illustrated on the uniform electron gas and the two-site Hubbard model.",
